National Security Advisor Jim Jones visited Colombia from August 6-8, 2010, to represent President Obama at the inauguration of Colombian President Juan Manuel Santos. Jones conveyed a clear message that the United States will maintain its close bilateral ties and strong partnership with Colombia. During his visit, Jones had productive discussions with President Santos and several new cabinet ministers, emphasizing the commitment to enhancing cooperation on various issues. The General expressed support for President Santos' efforts to improve relations with neighboring countries through direct dialogue based on mutual respect. Jones also met with outgoing President Alvaro Uribe to commend him and his government for their successful eight-year term and courageous leadership in bringing security and prosperity to the Colombian people.